It seems like your device (especially if it's an iPhone) or browser is blocking the automatic Full Screen mode, or you might be referring to the browser's address bar and navigation buttons taking up space.

I have made updates to help with this:

1.  **Strict Layout Locking**: I updated the CSS to strictly force the app to fit the window without scrolling the whole page.
2.  **Enhanced Full Screen Button**: I improved the "Tela Cheia" button logic.
    *   If your device supports it (Android/Desktop), it will hide the browser bars.
    *   **iPhone/iPad Users**: If you click the button and it doesn't work, a message will appear explaining that on iOS, the only way to get true full screen is to tap the **"Share" button** in Safari and select **"Add to Home Screen"**.
3.  **Visual Improvements**: The "Tela Cheia" button is now more visible.

